div.p:
His bed shall seem a
school, his board a
shrift;

With Cassio's suit:
therefore be merry,
Cassio;

Who steals my purse steals
trash; 'tis something,
nothing;

No, Iago; I'll see before
I doubt; when I doubt,
prove;

He thought 'twas
witchcraft-- but I am much
to blame;

I slept the next night
well, fed well, was free
and merry;

By the world, I think my
wife be honest and think
she is not;
